textBeforeTable: PHYS 329 - Atomic and Nuclear Physics (Spring 2011) PHYS 241 - College Physics I (Summer 2011) PHYS 281 - University Physics I (Spring 2011)  Courses Taught If you are a student at UW-Stout and have an interest in using computers to model the behaviors or properties of any systems, please stop by my office for a chat; there may be research opportunities available. My research interests lie in the field of computational modeling of various systems. My primary focus is modeling the magnetic properties of nanomagnetic materials, but I am interested in developing computer models for other types of systems, even those beyond the traditional realm of physics.
